article.description: — Dontarius James had a career-high 25 points as Jacksonville beat New Orleans 77-70 on Thursday.
article.headline: James lifts Jacksonville past New Orleans 77-70
article.linkText: James lifts Jacksonville past New Orleans 77-70
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Dontarius James had a career-high 25 points as Jacksonville beat New Orleans 77-70 on Thursday. Bryce Workman had 19 points and nine rebounds for Jacksonville (5-2). Tyreese Davis added 13 points and Trey Sides had 11 points. Troy Green had 24 points and eight rebounds for the Privateers (1-5). Damion Rosser scored a career-high 23 points and Ahren Freeman had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
